I really don't know why...

245
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:07,187
anyone would want
to take that urn.

246
00:21:07,188 --> 00:21:12,450
The only thing I know is that there was a name
on the coffin: Oscar de la Vallé.

247
00:21:12,451 --> 00:21:15,262
- Oscar de la Vallé?
- Yes.

248
00:21:15,263 --> 00:21:17,422
do you know who he was?

249
00:21:17,423 --> 00:21:21,040
The monsignor thought
it was the same man...

250
00:21:21,041 --> 00:21:26,112
who figures in an old story that's been
popular in Aosta for centuries.

251
00:21:26,113 --> 00:21:30,599
Most people, including me,
consider it nothing but legend.

252
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:34,764
Brusca didn't. That's why he sent
the items to you for verification.

253
00:21:34,765 --> 00:21:38,125
Well, can you tell me
about the story?

254
00:21:38,126 --> 00:21:40,028
In 1814...

255
00:21:40,029 --> 00:21:43,389
workers renovating
the church curia in Aosta...

256
00:21:43,390 --> 00:21:45,873
discovered an urn.

257
00:21:45,874 --> 00:21:48,685
There were several items inside it...

258
00:21:48,686 --> 00:21:52,267
including a dress that may have been
from pagan times.

259
00:21:52,268 --> 00:21:54,141
<i>[Wolves Growling]</i>

260
00:21:54,142 --> 00:21:57,531
<i>As the legend has it, packs of wolves
came out of the forest...</i>

261
00:21:57,532 --> 00:21:59,826
<i>the night after the urn
was found.</i>

262
00:21:59,827 --> 00:22:02,990
<i>They dug up freshly-buried
bodies in the graveyard...</i>

263
00:22:02,991 --> 00:22:05,056
<i>and tore them to bits.</i>

264
00:22:05,057 --> 00:22:06,985
The local priest decided
to send the urn to the Vatican.

265
00:22:06,986 --> 00:22:08,028
[Horse Neighing]

266
00:22:08,029 --> 00:22:10,771
<i>Oscar de la Vallé
volunteered to deliver it.</i>

267
00:22:10,772 --> 00:22:14,130
<i>He was a knight of noble birth.
Only he was allowed to talk with the pope.</i>

268
00:22:14,131 --> 00:22:18,137
<i>- [Woman Whimpering]
- He had one bad trip.</i>

269
00:22:18,138 --> 00:22:21,783
<i>Wherever he went,
death and destruction followed.</i>

270
00:22:21,784 --> 00:22:24,078
<i>Children died.
Crops burned.</i>

271
00:22:24,079 --> 00:22:27,597
<i>- Whole villages were devastated.
- [People Screaming]</i>

272
00:22:27,598 --> 00:22:30,407
<i>Many towns refused to let
De la Vallé enter.</i>

273
00:22:30,408 --> 00:22:32,988
<i>People were in a panic.</i>

274
00:22:32,989 --> 00:22:37,028
<i>By the time he reached Viterbo,
he was both sick and blind.</i>

275
00:22:37,064 --> 00:22:39,352
<i>The church took him in.</i>

276
00:22:39,353 --> 00:22:42,775
<i>He died six days later.
Maybe it was malarial fever.</i>

277
00:22:42,776 --> 00:22:45,068
<i>His body was buried
in a secret place.</i>

278
00:22:45,069 --> 00:22:50,065
<i>The urn was chained to his coffin
and sealed with crucifixes.</i>

279
00:22:51,398 --> 00:22:56,854
After the urn was found,
the monsignor was a different person.

280
00:22:56,855 --> 00:22:59,859
He began talking nonsense.

281
00:22:59,860 --> 00:23:01,925
[Sighs]

282
00:23:01,926 --> 00:23:04,929
Wait. Wait, wait.

283
00:23:04,930 --> 00:23:07,090
I- Yes-

284
00:23:07,091 --> 00:23:10,581
- He was writing this when he had the stroke.
- Here.

285
00:23:10,582 --> 00:23:15,480
It's a list of what was in the urn.

286
00:23:16,278 --> 00:23:19,961
- "Mater Lacrimarum. "
- Mater Lacrimarum. Yes.

287
00:23:19,962 --> 00:23:22,320
The monsignor thought the urn...

288
00:23:22,321 --> 00:23:25,518
and its contents were magical...

289
00:23:25,519 --> 00:23:27,456
that they belonged
to an evil witch...

290
00:23:27,457 --> 00:23:31,753
named Mater Lacrimarum-
the Mother of Tears.

291
00:23:31,754 --> 00:23:34,822
It's such a shame.

292
00:23:34,823 --> 00:23:37,406
He was a brilliant man- kind...

293
00:23:37,407 --> 00:23:40,475
<i>and a wonderful teacher.</i>

294
00:23:40,476 --> 00:23:43,706
To end his days believing
in this nonsense-

295
00:23:47,262 --> 00:23:51,462
<i>I'm sure he told you the same thing
he told me many times-</i>

296
00:23:51,463 --> 00:23:55,858
that God's plans for us are a mystery
to everyone but him.

297
00:23:55,859 --> 00:23:58,635
<i>Monsignor Brusca wrote this
for a reason.</i>

298
00:23:58,636 --> 00:24:03,641
One we might not understand,
but a reason nonetheless.

299
00:24:03,642 --> 00:24:06,087
Good-bye, Father.

300
00:24:10,395 --> 00:24:13,657
<i>[Dog Barking]</i>

301
00:24:34,437 --> 00:24:37,333
<i>[Engine Starts]</i>

302
00:24:38,446 --> 00:24:41,831
<i>[Thunderclap]</i>

303
00:24:43,716 --> 00:24:45,591
- [Men Panting]
- [Gasps]

304
00:24:45,592 --> 00:24:48,438
[Man]
Hold still. I said hold still!

305
00:24:48,439 --> 00:24:51,963
- No! Help me!
- Open your legs. Open your legs!

306
00:24:51,964 --> 00:24:55,347
No! Help me!

307
00:25:26,597 --> 00:25:29,012
<i>[Opening Drawer]</i>

308
00:25:58,381 --> 00:26:01,318
[Sighs]

309
00:26:04,851 --> 00:26:07,265
[Sniffles]

310
00:26:11,710 --> 00:26:14,235
<i>- [Siren Wailing]
- Stop! Freeze!</i>

311
00:26:14,236 --> 00:26:18,182
- Freeze!
- [Man Groans]

312
00:26:18,183 --> 00:26:21,029
<i>[Tires Screeching]</i>

313
00:26:22,713 --> 00:26:24,721
<i>[Gunshot]</i>

314
00:26:24,722 --> 00:26:28,109
[Keys Jangling]

315
00:26:28,670 --> 00:26:32,054
<i>[Siren Wailing]</i>

316
00:26:39,028 --> 00:26:41,443
Michael?

317
00:26:47,023 --> 00:26:48,965
<i>Hello?</i>

318
00:26:48,966 --> 00:26:51,713
Is there anybody home?

319
00:26:59,182 --> 00:27:01,597
Michael?

320
00:27:06,953 --> 00:27:09,369
Paul?

321
00:27:20,477 --> 00:27:22,895
Michael?

322
00:27:24,684 --> 00:27:28,503
Michael! What happened?

323
00:27:28,504 --> 00:27:31,349
They took him.

324
00:27:31,350 --> 00:27:33,651
<i>- Who took him?
- The babysitter...</i>

325
00:27:33,652 --> 00:27:37,662
went out for two minutes, she said.

326
00:27:37,663 --> 00:27:39,865
She came back...

327
00:27:39,866 --> 00:27:43,384
and she found... this-

328
00:27:44,059 --> 00:27:47,231
<i>"If you want to see
your son again...</i>

329
00:27:47,232 --> 00:27:49,372
<i>keep the silentium. "</i>

330
00:27:49,373 --> 00:27:51,445
<i>The silentium.</i>

331
00:27:51,446 --> 00:27:54,231
Michael, I'm sorry.

332
00:27:54,232 --> 00:27:57,119
I'm so sorry, darling.

333
00:27:57,120 --> 00:28:00,098
<i>Those symbols-
they are the same ones I saw on the urn.</i>

334
00:28:00,099 --> 00:28:04,891
<i>I know! It's the same people.
It's some kind of black magic.</i>

335
00:28:04,892 --> 00:28:06,932
Black magic?

336
00:28:06,967 --> 00:28:09,093
- I don't know about black magic-
- What?

337
00:28:09,094 --> 00:28:11,709
What, you think this is all some
sort of coincidence?

338
00:28:11,710 --> 00:28:14,507
- No, I didn't say-
- don't be so bloody naive! Giselle's dead.

339
00:28:14,508 --> 00:28:16,870
Brusca's in a coma.
Now they've taken Paul.

340
00:28:16,871 --> 00:28:19,793
It's - It's all connected with the urn
and-and those talismans.

341
00:28:19,794 --> 00:28:23,032
And they want me to stop looking.
They want me to keep quiet.

342
00:28:23,033 --> 00:28:26,664
About what?
Keep quiet about what?

343
00:28:26,665 --> 00:28:31,104
The darkness... gathering around Rome.
You haven't seen it?

344
00:28:31,105 --> 00:28:33,503
It's happening.
Here, come with me!

345
00:28:33,504 --> 00:28:36,226
- Look. Let me show you. Look.
- I'm coming.

346
00:28:36,227 --> 00:28:39,207
What do you think all this is?
Where is it?

347
00:28:39,208 --> 00:28:43,390
- An epidemic of suicides, 52 in two days!
- Yes.

348
00:28:43,391 --> 00:28:46,112
Look. A wave of violence
spreads through the city-

349
00:28:46,113 --> 00:28:48,868
murders, fires, kidnappings,
church vandalism-

350
00:28:48,869 --> 00:28:51,586
Yes, Michael, you're scaring me.
I- I know all this.

351
00:28:51,587 --> 00:28:54,541
I'm going to Monteleone.
There's a priest there, Father Johannes.

352
00:28:54,542 --> 00:28:57,359
And what on earth could he do
to help this situation?

353
00:28:57,360 --> 00:28:59,565
He's an exorcist-
one of the last confirmed by the Vatican.

354
00:28:59,566 --> 00:29:01,735
He knows more about the occult
than anyone else I know.

355
00:29:01,736 --> 00:29:04,816
And he'll be able to help me get Paul
back in a way they can't detect.

356
00:29:04,817 --> 00:29:08,057
- Look, Michael, why don't we try the police?
- No! No police!

357
00:29:08,058 --> 00:29:12,302
You saw the way they looked at you at the
museum. They thought you were fucking crazy!

358
00:29:12,303 --> 00:29:14,896
Michael, look, I-I love Paul,
okay, as much as you do...

359
00:29:14,897 --> 00:29:17,362
but I don't know if
this is the best way-

360
00:29:17,363 --> 00:29:20,536
He is my son!

361
00:29:20,537 --> 00:29:22,959
Not yours!

362
00:29:24,352 --> 00:29:27,536
<i>- Michael.
- [Door Shuts]</i>

363
00:29:35,712 --> 00:29:38,503
[Women Cheering, Chattering]

364
00:29:38,504 --> 00:29:41,879
Damn it!
Be careful, damn it!

365
00:29:41,880 --> 00:29:44,313
You rot in hell.
[Growls]

366
00:29:44,314 --> 00:29:46,586
[Laughs]

367
00:29:46,587 --> 00:29:48,855
[All Chattering, Squealing]

368
00:29:48,856 --> 00:29:52,033
- Are you ready for the celebration?
- Of course!

369
00:29:57,263 --> 00:30:00,020
- Excuse me.
- [Shrieking]

370
00:30:00,021 --> 00:30:02,388
[Laughs]

371
00:30:26,198 --> 00:30:29,137
<i>Three Furies.</i>

372
00:30:29,865 --> 00:30:32,235
Furies.

373
00:30:36,947 --> 00:30:39,436
Three Fates.

374
00:30:40,774 --> 00:30:42,432
Three Graces.

375
00:30:42,433 --> 00:30:47,292
<i>Diana, the three-headed-</i>

376
00:30:53,799 --> 00:30:55,845
The Triad.

377
00:30:55,846 --> 00:30:58,343
Why are they always three?

378
00:30:58,344 --> 00:31:00,559
[Phone Buzzing]

379
00:31:00,560 --> 00:31:03,941
Sorry. Hello?

380
00:31:03,942 --> 00:31:06,707
- Sarah, hi. It's me. It's Michael.
- Michael?

381
00:31:06,708 --> 00:31:09,501
- Where are you?
- Wait, no, no. Wait, wait, listen.

382
00:31:09,502 --> 00:31:12,232
- I-I really need your help, okay?
- Yeah, of course I'll help you.

383
00:31:12,233 --> 00:31:14,377
Just tell me what to do.

384
00:31:14,378 --> 00:31:17,338
- No, you've got-
- Michael?

385
00:31:17,339 --> 00:31:19,515
Michael!

386
00:31:19,516 --> 00:31:23,055
Hello, are you there?
Michael!

387
00:31:24,978 --> 00:31:27,027
<i>[Horn Honking]</i>

388
00:31:27,028 --> 00:31:30,667
<i>Help me, Sarah.
Help me.</i>

389
00:31:30,668 --> 00:31:32,781
Michael, are you still there?

390
00:31:32,782 --> 00:31:36,188
Michael? Michael!

391
00:31:58,734 --> 00:32:03,410
<i>[Woman Over P.A. Speaking Italian]</i>

392
00:32:05,091 --> 00:32:09,265
- [Laughing]
- Whoo-hoo!

393
00:32:10,005 --> 00:32:11,854
Hey, sister.

394
00:32:11,855 --> 00:32:14,948
<i>[Laughter Continues]</i>

395
00:32:15,304 --> 00:32:17,807
[Man Laughing]

396
00:32:17,842 --> 00:32:20,311
[Laughter Stops]

397
00:32:23,256 --> 00:32:25,636
Chotomateh!

398
00:32:32,326 --> 00:32:34,823
Simone. Ikeh!

399
00:33:13,136 --> 00:33:17,183
<i>[Laughing]</i>

400
00:33:26,516 --> 00:33:28,444
Okay, please, come on.
Let's find her.

401
00:33:28,445 --> 00:33:31,110
And try not to draw too much
attention to yourselves, okay?

402
00:33:31,111 --> 00:33:34,232
- Okay, I know, I know.
- Okay, you two with me. Come on. This way.

403
00:33:34,233 --> 00:33:36,861
Move! Move!

404
00:33:51,052 --> 00:33:53,142
<i>[Man]
People, we're the police.</i>

405
00:33:53,143 --> 00:33:55,874
<i>No, no, no, you can't go in.
Can't go in.</i>

406
00:33:55,875 --> 00:34:00,054
<i>Lady, you too. Move on, please.
Thank you. Move on.</i>

407
00:34:03,886 --> 00:34:07,928
[Panting]

408
00:34:31,281 --> 00:34:33,986
<i>- [Woman's Voice] Concentrate.
- Huh?</i>

409
00:34:33,987 --> 00:34:36,724
<i>Concentrate!</i>

410
00:34:38,211 --> 00:34:40,875
<i>They won't see you!</i>

411
00:34:41,591 --> 00:34:44,844
<i>Don't worry.
They won't see you!</i>

412
00:35:24,505 --> 00:35:27,660
We lost her.

413
00:35:27,661 --> 00:35:30,717
[No Audible dialogue]

414
00:35:31,270 --> 00:35:33,674
Okay.

415
00:36:01,040 --> 00:36:03,230
[Sighs]

416
00:36:03,231 --> 00:36:07,249
[Panting]

417
00:36:08,903 --> 00:36:11,157
[Coughs]

418
00:36:11,158 --> 00:36:13,560
[Shouts]
What?

419
00:36:28,170 --> 00:36:31,056
[Horn Honks]

420
00:36:33,356 --> 00:36:37,057
<i>[Woman Over P.A. Speaking Italian]</i>

421
00:36:37,897 --> 00:36:40,023
Excuse me.
Where's this train going?

422
00:36:40,024 --> 00:36:43,661
- Orte. Leaves in 30 minutes.
- Thank you.

423
00:36:57,488 --> 00:36:59,805
- Michael?
- This is Michael Pierce's voicemail.

424
00:36:59,806 --> 00:37:02,126
- Please leave a message after the tone.
- [Tone Beeps]

425
00:37:02,127 --> 00:37:05,573
Michael, I've run into problems.
I'm going to Monteleone.

426
00:37:05,574 --> 00:37:07,980
Bye.

427
00:37:33,215 --> 00:37:36,023
- Can I help you?
- [Speaking Japanese]

428
00:37:38,675 --> 00:37:41,295
Sorry, I don't understand.

429
00:37:41,296 --> 00:37:43,874
[Japanese]

430
00:37:43,875 --> 00:37:46,938
- [Gagging]
- [Laughs]

431
00:37:48,369 --> 00:37:51,659
[Japanese]

432
00:37:51,660 --> 00:37:54,054
[Laughs]

433
00:37:54,055 --> 00:37:56,761
[Shuddering]

434
00:38:30,269 --> 00:38:33,749
- [Chuckles]
- Get out!

435
00:38:43,484 --> 00:38:46,388
<i>[Woman Over P.A.] The train for Monteleone
now leaving on track nine.</i>

436
00:38:46,389 --> 00:38:50,102
<i>- [Marchi] Where the fuck is she?
- Maybe in there.</i>

437
00:38:50,103 --> 00:38:53,651
<i>- Maybe she's in there!
- [Whistles Blowing]</i>

438
00:39:10,397 --> 00:39:14,211
Well, Sarah Mandy killed
this woman because she saw...

439
00:39:14,212 --> 00:39:18,027
Miss Mandy attacking
da Silva over there.

440
00:39:18,028 --> 00:39:20,902
As simple as this.

441
00:39:23,542 --> 00:39:28,527
Mandy weighs 110 pounds,
at the most?

442
00:39:28,528 --> 00:39:32,391
da Silva, God rest his soul,
was a fucking gorilla.

443
00:39:32,392 --> 00:39:34,506
And he was armed.

444
00:39:34,507 --> 00:39:37,911
No, there's more to this case
than we think.

445
00:39:37,912 --> 00:39:39,953
Can you move them back, please?

446
00:39:49,419 --> 00:39:54,725
<i>[Woman Shouting]
Nafech! Nafech! Nafech!</i>

447
00:39:54,726 --> 00:39:58,040
Nafech! Nafech!
Nafech! Nafech!

448
00:39:58,041 --> 00:40:00,104
<i>Nafech! Nafech!</i>

449
00:40:00,105 --> 00:40:03,740
Nafech! Nafech!

450
00:40:03,741 --> 00:40:05,928
<i>[Woman Continues Shouting]</i>

451
00:40:05,929 --> 00:40:08,725
<i>Nafech! Nafech!</i>

452
00:40:11,887 --> 00:40:14,289
[Bell Rings]

453
00:40:23,828 --> 00:40:25,724
<i>- Yes?
- Hello?</i>

454
00:40:25,761 --> 00:40:28,943
My name is Sarah Mandy. I'm looking
for a friend of mine, Michael Pierce.

455
00:40:28,944 --> 00:40:33,064
- He came to see Father Johannes.
- No, I'm sorry, he's not here.

456
00:40:33,065 --> 00:40:34,996
What?

457
00:40:34,997 --> 00:40:38,308
Could I see Father Johannes then?
It's very important.

458
00:40:38,309 --> 00:40:40,340
You have to come back tomorrow.

459
00:40:40,341 --> 00:40:43,173
- He can't see you today.
- I'm sorry, but that's not possible.

460
00:40:43,208 --> 00:40:46,362
Please, tell him
I won't take much of his time.

461
00:40:46,363 --> 00:40:48,766
Please.

462
00:40:49,417 --> 00:40:51,604
All right. Come in.

463
00:40:51,605 --> 00:40:54,588
Thanks. Thanks a lot.

464
00:40:58,300 --> 00:41:01,668
<i>[Clock Chiming]</i>

465
00:41:15,978 --> 00:41:19,340
You look like you had
a hard trip.

466
00:41:22,672 --> 00:41:25,016
You have it, you know.

467
00:41:25,017 --> 00:41:27,457
Your mother's gaze.

468
00:41:28,528 --> 00:41:31,644
You're Elisa Mandy's daughter,
aren't you?

469
00:41:33,422 --> 00:41:35,821
<i>I'm Marta Colussi.</i>

470
00:41:40,212 --> 00:41:42,844
You really look just like her.

471
00:41:43,605 --> 00:41:49,224
I knew your mother
many years ago in Germany.

472
00:41:49,225 --> 00:41:51,693
She was a wonderful teacher.

473
00:41:51,978 --> 00:41:54,432
<i>I learned so much from her.</i>

474
00:41:54,433 --> 00:41:58,217
<i>She was a great spiritualist-
the best I've ever known.</i>

475
00:41:58,218 --> 00:42:02,164
- My mother was a dancer.
- And a healer.

476
00:42:02,165 --> 00:42:04,875
A white witch, if you will.

477
00:42:05,979 --> 00:42:09,564
And it seems to me
you've inherited some of her gifts.

478
00:42:09,565 --> 00:42:12,737
- Listen, lady-
- It's Marta.

479
00:42:12,738 --> 00:42:15,034
Marta. Whoever you are...

480
00:42:15,035 --> 00:42:17,057
I don't know you and I didn't
come here to talk to you.

481
00:42:17,058 --> 00:42:19,777
Please leave me
alone now, okay?

482
00:42:19,779 --> 00:42:23,859
How did you get away
at the train station?

483
00:42:25,642 --> 00:42:28,453
What the-Who are you?

484
00:42:29,313 --> 00:42:35,241
Elisa was helping you.
Coaching you, wasn't she?

485
00:42:35,265 --> 00:42:37,335
I- I don't know.

486
00:42:37,336 --> 00:42:41,369
I heard- I heard a voice.

487
00:42:44,291 --> 00:42:48,137
- did you really know my mother?
- Quite well.

488
00:42:48,138 --> 00:42:52,252
- You don't know much about her, do you?
- No.

489
00:42:52,253 --> 00:42:56,053
I don't remember much
about my parents.

490
00:42:56,054 --> 00:42:58,930
I was very young
when they died in the accident.

491
00:43:00,044 --> 00:43:03,076
The car crash in Freiburg.

492
00:43:03,933 --> 00:43:09,230
No, honey. I'm sorry.
That's not what happened.

493
00:43:11,717 --> 00:43:15,085
- Your parents were murdered.
- What?

494
00:43:15,120 --> 00:43:18,485
What are you talking about?

495
00:43:18,488 --> 00:43:22,209
Nobody ever told me this.
What are you saying?

496
00:43:27,405 --> 00:43:32,081
Your mother dared to fight
a very powerful black witch:

497
00:43:32,082 --> 00:43:36,296
Mater Suspiriorum,
the Mother of Sighs.

498
00:43:36,297 --> 00:43:38,424
The Mother of Sighs?

499
00:43:38,425 --> 00:43:41,379
<i>[Man Coughing]</i>

500
00:43:44,780 --> 00:43:47,008
Father Johannes.

501
00:43:47,759 --> 00:43:50,871
- How many drops?
- Twenty, please.

502
00:43:50,872 --> 00:43:54,886
You look exhausted.
You need to rest.

503
00:43:54,887 --> 00:43:57,091
With everything that's going on now?
I have to fight.

504
00:43:57,092 --> 00:44:01,453
- I have to fight!
- Stay calm now. Please. Take your drops.

505
00:44:02,209 --> 00:44:05,995
Your weakness is your strength, Father.

506
00:44:09,033 --> 00:44:12,368
I've been expecting you.

507
00:44:13,056 --> 00:44:15,394
- You're Sarah.
- Yes.

508
00:44:15,429 --> 00:44:17,812
Hi.

509
00:44:19,624 --> 00:44:22,862
<i>There's a lot I have to
tell you-about your mother...</i>

510
00:44:22,863 --> 00:44:26,884
<i>about you,
and about a world-</i>

511
00:44:26,885 --> 00:44:29,248
[Laughs]
you hardly know.

512
00:44:30,029 --> 00:44:32,070
<i>More than a thousand years ago...</i>

513
00:44:32,071 --> 00:44:34,629
witchcraft was birthed...

514
00:44:34,630 --> 00:44:38,328
by the shores of the Black Sea
by three sisters.

515
00:44:38,329 --> 00:44:40,887
<i>For years they roamed
the earth...</i>

516
00:44:40,888 --> 00:44:45,261
bringing death and destruction
wherever they went.

517
00:44:45,262 --> 00:44:50,028
Search any art history book
and you'll find images of them.

518
00:44:50,029 --> 00:44:51,907
Eventually, they found homes.

519
00:44:51,908 --> 00:44:57,418
<i>Mater Suspiriorum, the Mother of Sighs,
settled in Freiburg.</i>

520
00:44:57,419 --> 00:45:01,891
<i>The Mother of Pain, Mater Tenebrarum,
went to New York.</i>

521
00:45:01,892 --> 00:45:05,134
<i>Mater Lacrimarum
came to Rome.</i>

522
00:45:05,135 --> 00:45:07,325
She's known as the Mother of Tears.

523
00:45:07,326 --> 00:45:10,189
She's the most cruel
and beautiful of the three.

524
00:45:10,190 --> 00:45:13,159
<i>And she's the only one still alive.</i>

525
00:45:13,160 --> 00:45:16,565
Mater Tenebrarum
and Mater Suspiriorum...

526
00:45:16,566 --> 00:45:18,513
<i>died many years ago.</i>

527
00:45:18,514 --> 00:45:22,145
The Mother of Sighs.
She murdered my parents.

528
00:45:22,146 --> 00:45:24,998
Yes. But not before your mother...

529
00:45:24,999 --> 00:45:26,944
<i>had injured her horribly.</i>

530
00:45:26,945 --> 00:45:31,874
<i>After fighting your mother,
she was reduced to a shell of her former self.</i>

531
00:45:31,875 --> 00:45:35,738
A young dancer
named Suzy Bannion...

532
00:45:35,739 --> 00:45:38,878
finally managed to kill her.

533
00:45:39,662 --> 00:45:42,158
But that's all history.

534
00:45:42,159 --> 00:45:45,047
When that urn Brusca
found was opened...

535
00:45:45,048 --> 00:45:48,256
it restored the Mother of Tears's powers.

536
00:45:48,257 --> 00:45:50,462
How do you know about that?

537
00:45:50,463 --> 00:45:54,128
Your friend, Michael,
told me about it...

538
00:45:54,129 --> 00:45:58,236
when he phoned and spoke
of a magic red tunic...

539
00:45:58,237 --> 00:46:01,092
that would be a great
and powerful talisman.

540
00:46:01,093 --> 00:46:04,305
I've had visions.
Witches are coming...

541
00:46:04,306 --> 00:46:07,487
from all over the world
to celebrate her return.

542
00:46:07,488 --> 00:46:10,443
Yes. They're arriving
in Rome every day.

543
00:46:10,444 --> 00:46:12,680
Every jet, every car...

544
00:46:12,681 --> 00:46:14,758
every train brings more.

545
00:46:14,759 --> 00:46:17,516
They aim to make Rome fall again...

546
00:46:17,517 --> 00:46:21,381
to usher in the Second Age of Witches.

547
00:46:21,382 --> 00:46:25,036
[Groans] I can't take it anymore.
I feel like I'm going crazy.

548
00:46:25,037 --> 00:46:28,086
There's nothing wrong
with your mind, Sarah.

549
00:46:28,087 --> 00:46:31,331
It's the world that's gone crazy.

550
00:46:32,036 --> 00:46:34,495
Have a look.

551
00:46:36,946 --> 00:46:39,381
Look at this.

552
00:46:39,382 --> 00:46:43,642
<i>Usually I have one exorcism request
a month...</i>

553
00:46:43,643 --> 00:46:48,520
but the last few days, I've had more cases
than I've had in my whole life.

554
00:46:48,521 --> 00:46:51,994
Every priest I talk to is faced
with the same challenge.

555
00:46:51,995 --> 00:46:53,720
[All Shouting]

556
00:46:53,721 --> 00:46:55,638
Why is all this happening?

557
00:46:55,639 --> 00:46:59,442
The Mother of Tears
spreads evil wherever she can.

558
00:46:59,443 --> 00:47:03,700
Some she kills,
others she drives mad.

559
00:47:03,701 --> 00:47:06,693
She revels in chaos
and human despair.

560
00:47:06,694 --> 00:47:09,325
[Shouting, Moaning]

561
00:47:09,326 --> 00:47:11,275
<i>We have work to do.</i>

562
00:47:11,276 --> 00:47:15,201
I have a book in my study
that shows us the way.

563
00:47:23,412 --> 00:47:26,596
[Panting]

564
00:47:33,605 --> 00:47:37,285
Valeria! Valeria!

565
00:47:37,286 --> 00:47:40,051
Valeria.

566
00:47:41,454 --> 00:47:44,316
<i>[Moaning]</i>

567
00:47:44,351 --> 00:47:48,158
<i>[Woman Sobbing]</i>

568
00:47:52,255 --> 00:47:54,631
Valeria.

569
00:47:59,385 --> 00:48:02,084
Requiescat!

570
00:48:03,539 --> 00:48:06,373
[Groans]

571
00:48:06,374 --> 00:48:09,624
[Gagging]

572
00:48:14,925 --> 00:48:16,398
[Screaming]

573
00:48:19,413 --> 00:48:21,818
Father Johannes!

574
00:48:23,468 --> 00:48:26,649
[Gasps, Screaming]

575
00:48:27,299 --> 00:48:30,214
[Screaming]

576
00:48:34,976 --> 00:48:38,718
- Mother?
- Marta, come back! Come back!

577
00:48:38,719 --> 00:48:42,424
[Sobbing]
Mother, I obeyed you!

578
00:48:43,355 --> 00:48:45,392
Come on, let's go!

579
00:48:47,385 --> 00:48:50,730
<i>[People Wailing, Screaming]</i>

580
00:48:53,907 --> 00:48:56,014
[Wailing, Screaming Continues]

581
00:48:56,015 --> 00:48:58,797
Let me- Somebody help-

582
00:48:58,798 --> 00:49:01,898
Marta!
Marta, help me!

583
00:49:01,899 --> 00:49:05,245
Oh, my God!

584
00:49:07,015 --> 00:49:10,982
Marta! Marta, let's go!

585
00:49:10,983 --> 00:49:13,912
[Screaming]

586
00:49:14,881 --> 00:49:16,800
- Where's your car?
- It's right there.

587
00:49:16,801 --> 00:49:19,185
They're coming!
Oh, God, run!

588
00:49:20,444 --> 00:49:22,363
It's locked!
Open- Open up!

589
00:49:22,364 --> 00:49:26,254
- Open it!
- I can't find my key!

590
00:49:27,928 --> 00:49:31,021
<i>[Keys Fall To Ground]</i>

591
00:49:44,363 --> 00:49:46,406
<i>Why were they all after me?</i>

592
00:49:46,407 --> 00:49:48,356
- Your mother.
- [Beeping]

593
00:49:48,357 --> 00:49:51,059
- What are you doing?
- I'm calling Michael.

594
00:49:51,094 --> 00:49:53,760
Are you crazy?
They can trace you with it.

595
00:49:53,761 --> 00:49:56,695
You're right.
Fuck it.

596
00:50:00,091 --> 00:50:02,936
Come to my place tonight.
It'll be safer for you.

597
00:50:02,937 --> 00:50:04,854
No, I'd rather go home.

598
00:50:04,855 --> 00:50:06,803
Michael can reach me there.

599
00:50:06,804 --> 00:50:08,725
Mmm.

600
00:50:08,726 --> 00:50:11,313
Here's my phone number
and address.

601
00:50:11,314 --> 00:50:14,287
- Call me anytime. It's no bother.
- Thank you.

602
00:50:14,288 --> 00:50:17,963
You're Elisa's daughter.
That's closer than family.

603
00:50:17,964 --> 00:50:21,480
I don't mean to scare you, but...

604
00:50:21,481 --> 00:50:23,399
they know who you are, Sarah.

605
00:50:23,400 --> 00:50:26,277
Promise me
you won't trust anyone.

606
00:50:26,278 --> 00:50:28,662
I promise.

607
00:50:31,267 --> 00:50:34,271
<i>- [Sirens Wailing]
- [People Shouting]</i>

608
00:50:34,272 --> 00:50:36,252
What's going on here?

609
00:50:36,253 --> 00:50:39,032
<i>[Marta]
They are burning the churches.</i>

610
00:50:39,033 --> 00:50:41,423
<i>It's getting worse.</i>

611
00:50:53,041 --> 00:50:56,714
[Gasping, Groaning]

612
00:51:03,557 --> 00:51:06,622
Mater! Mater!

613
00:51:22,520 --> 00:51:24,820
[Whirring]

614
00:51:24,821 --> 00:51:27,687
<i>- [Whirring Continues]
- [Slam]</i>

615
00:51:48,576 --> 00:51:51,446
[Gasps]

616
00:52:05,077 --> 00:52:07,790
[Gasps Loudly]

617
00:52:17,353 --> 00:52:21,702
<i>[Groaning, Whispering]</i>

618
00:52:21,703 --> 00:52:23,363
[Gasps]

619
00:52:23,364 --> 00:52:27,039
<i>[Groaning,
Whispering Continue]</i>

620
00:52:38,234 --> 00:52:42,196
[Creature Growling]

621
00:52:42,197 --> 00:52:45,543
[Gasping, Panting]

622
00:52:46,353 --> 00:52:48,528
<i>[Sarah]
There was somebody at my apartment!</i>

623
00:52:48,529 --> 00:52:52,109
I saw lights and shadows under the door.
I feel like I'm going crazy!

624
00:52:52,110 --> 00:52:56,074
God! Help. Please help me.
Help me, please.

625
00:52:56,075 --> 00:52:58,462
Take a deep breath.

626
00:53:02,980 --> 00:53:05,857
- Thank you.
- Calm down.

627
00:53:05,858 --> 00:53:08,243
Come in.

628
00:53:09,887 --> 00:53:12,285
- Elga, meet Sarah.
- Hi.

629
00:53:12,286 --> 00:53:14,584
- What is she doing here?
- It's okay.

630
00:53:14,585 --> 00:53:17,466
Marta, you have to help me.
I don't know what's happening to me.

631
00:53:17,467 --> 00:53:20,053
- Come with me.
- You have to explain.

632
00:53:20,054 --> 00:53:21,973
Why is all this happening to me?
Why?

633
00:53:21,974 --> 00:53:24,849
They know who you are.
They can't take any chances.

634
00:53:24,850 --> 00:53:28,015
But I- I-
I don't know anything.

635
00:53:28,016 --> 00:53:30,892
You know more
than you think you do.

636
00:53:30,893 --> 00:53:34,688
How else have you survived
this long with those monsters after you?

637
00:53:40,456 --> 00:53:43,328
Elga, would you please
excuse us for a minute?

638
00:53:43,329 --> 00:53:45,250
Oh, please. Come on.

639
00:53:45,251 --> 00:53:47,637
Please?

640
00:53:52,732 --> 00:53:55,385
You have gifts, Sarah.

641
00:53:55,386 --> 00:53:59,059
You need to accept that
if you want to survive.

642
00:54:10,444 --> 00:54:15,144
[Speaking Ancient Language]

643
00:54:18,726 --> 00:54:22,073
[Continues In Ancient Language]

644
00:54:23,648 --> 00:54:26,712
Watch and learn.

645
00:54:42,610 --> 00:54:45,158
drifting spirits.

646
00:54:45,839 --> 00:54:49,633
They are everywhere,
especially here in Rome.

647
00:54:51,498 --> 00:54:53,962
<i>[Marta]
The old houses are full of ghosts.</i>

648
00:54:53,963 --> 00:54:55,880
Think about it.

649
00:54:55,881 --> 00:54:58,851
The city is 2700 years old...

650
00:54:58,852 --> 00:55:02,687
and we are standing
on five layers of graves.

651
00:55:02,688 --> 00:55:05,726
- How do you do it?
- You can do it too.

652
00:55:05,727 --> 00:55:09,367
<i>With your gifts,
you can see what others can't.</i>

653
00:55:14,934 --> 00:55:17,487
Close your eyes.

654
00:55:19,539 --> 00:55:22,384
Focus all of your energy...

655
00:55:22,385 --> 00:55:25,992
and concentrate on this spot.

656
00:55:27,117 --> 00:55:29,602
- [Gasps]
- Good.

657
00:55:30,508 --> 00:55:34,149
Now just do like I did
and blow.

658
00:55:54,135 --> 00:55:56,436
<i>[Sarah Gasps]</i>

659
00:55:56,437 --> 00:55:58,484
Sarah.

660
00:55:58,485 --> 00:56:00,871
No, it can't be.

661
00:56:01,649 --> 00:56:03,632
Mommy?

662
00:56:03,633 --> 00:56:05,996
Sarah. Ohh.

663
00:56:05,997 --> 00:56:08,875
- Mommy!
- You can't touch her or she'll disappear.

664
00:56:08,876 --> 00:56:10,760
Leave me alone.

665
00:56:10,761 --> 00:56:15,429
Mater Lacrimarum grows stronger.
She grows stronger, Sarah!

666
00:56:15,430 --> 00:56:17,315
Where-Where are you?

667
00:56:17,316 --> 00:56:20,034
Mommy! Mommy!

668
00:56:20,035 --> 00:56:22,972
You're in great danger,
my dear child.

669
00:56:22,973 --> 00:56:25,245
<i>- Learn to fight.
- No!</i>

670
00:56:25,246 --> 00:56:26,845
No! No!

671
00:56:26,846 --> 00:56:30,743
<i>Don't go, Mommy!
Don't leave me! Mommy, please!</i>

672
00:56:30,744 --> 00:56:33,175
Mommy!
[Sobbing]

673
00:56:33,176 --> 00:56:35,443
Please make her come back.
Please!

674
00:56:35,444 --> 00:56:37,237
Mo-
[Sobbing]

675
00:56:37,238 --> 00:56:40,298
<i>Don't leave me.
Don't leave.</i>

676
00:56:47,112 --> 00:56:49,419
She told me to fight.

677
00:56:49,420 --> 00:56:53,604
You have to help me.
I have to fight. Please.

678
00:56:54,566 --> 00:56:57,283
I'm only a psychic.

679
00:56:57,284 --> 00:57:02,710
I can communicate with spirits,
but that's about it.

680
00:57:03,678 --> 00:57:06,877
I don't have your mother's gifts,
or yours.

681
00:57:06,878 --> 00:57:08,791
[Whimpers]

682
00:57:08,792 --> 00:57:12,631
You need someone who can guide you,
point you in the right direction.

683
00:57:12,632 --> 00:57:14,901
Yes.

684
00:57:14,902 --> 00:57:18,066
Tomorrow I'll introduce you
to Guglielmo de Witt.

685
00:57:18,067 --> 00:57:20,877
- He's a great Belgian thinker.
- Okay.

686
00:57:20,878 --> 00:57:25,609
He'll tell you something useful,
if it's not too late.

687
00:57:28,780 --> 00:57:31,413
Thank you.

688
00:57:31,414 --> 00:57:34,661
Oh, thank you.
[Sobbing Continues]

689
00:57:34,662 --> 00:57:38,430
[Moaning]

690
00:57:47,018 --> 00:57:48,366
[Groaning]

691
00:57:48,367 --> 00:57:50,916
No.

692
00:57:51,317 --> 00:57:54,689
No.
[Gasps, Panting]

693
00:57:59,689 --> 00:58:02,454
[Gasps]

694
00:58:02,489 --> 00:58:05,654
[Panting]

695
00:58:07,290 --> 00:58:09,254
[Shrieking]

696
00:58:09,272 --> 00:58:11,489
[Gasps]

697
00:58:27,338 --> 00:58:30,738
[Chittering]

698
00:59:06,149 --> 00:59:09,297
[Chittering Continues]

699
00:59:13,049 --> 00:59:14,997
[Shrieking]

700
00:59:31,955 --> 00:59:34,191
<i>[Phone Ringing]</i>

701
00:59:35,400 --> 00:59:38,160
<i>[Ringing Continues]</i>

702
00:59:38,780 --> 00:59:41,021
- [Line Ringing]
- Pick up the phone.

703
00:59:41,022 --> 00:59:44,144
Come on, Marta,
pick up the phone!

704
00:59:44,145 --> 00:59:47,088
<i>[Ringing Continues]</i>

705
00:59:48,400 --> 00:59:49,732
[Gasps]

706
00:59:49,733 --> 00:59:53,655
[Screaming]

707
00:59:54,933 --> 00:59:57,305
Hello? Hello, Marta?

708
00:59:57,306 --> 01:00:02,407
Marta, you have to get out of there now!
Marta? Hello? Who's there?

709
01:00:02,408 --> 01:00:05,102
Run! It's too late!

710
01:00:05,103 --> 01:00:06,989
Now! Run now!

711
01:00:06,990 --> 01:00:11,400
[Shrieking]

712
01:00:11,605 --> 01:00:14,364
[Shrieking Continues]

713
01:00:26,813 --> 01:00:30,672
[Gasping, Screaming]

714
01:00:31,333 --> 01:00:33,607
<i>- No! She doesn't know anything!
- [Shrieking]</i>

715
01:00:33,608 --> 01:00:35,817
No! don't do it!
don't do it!

716
01:00:35,818 --> 01:00:38,220
[Screaming]

717
01:00:42,222 --> 01:00:46,242
- [Shrieking Continues]
- [Screaming Continues]

718
01:00:49,012 --> 01:00:50,983
[Screaming Stops]

719
01:01:14,058 --> 01:01:15,976
[Shrieking]

720
01:01:17,058 --> 01:01:19,376
[Grunting, Groaning]

721
01:01:19,377 --> 01:01:21,690
[Groaning Continues]

722
01:01:21,691 --> 01:01:24,775
- [Guttural Chuckling]
- [Bones Snapping]

723
01:01:25,843 --> 01:01:29,208
[Gasping, Coughing]

724
01:01:34,140 --> 01:01:37,905
[Screams, Wheezing, Groaning]

725
01:01:37,906 --> 01:01:40,253
Mater! Mater!

726
01:01:40,254 --> 01:01:42,538
Where is Sarah?

727
01:01:42,539 --> 01:01:44,593
[Whimpering]
She isn't here.

728
01:01:44,594 --> 01:01:47,032
Idiot!

729
01:01:51,232 --> 01:01:56,047
- [Shrieking]
- It is you.

730
01:01:56,048 --> 01:01:59,396
It is.
[Wheezing]

731
01:02:02,675 --> 01:02:06,708
[Moaning]
[Laughing]

732
01:02:08,058 --> 01:02:09,976
[Shrieking]

733
01:02:14,650 --> 01:02:16,985
<i>[Cat Yowls]</i>

734
01:02:16,986 --> 01:02:19,853
[Laughing]

735
01:02:27,608 --> 01:02:30,485
<i>Stay strong. Stay strong!</i>

736
01:02:30,486 --> 01:02:33,141
- Mom.
- Stay strong, Sarah!

737
01:02:33,142 --> 01:02:36,335
Yes.

738
01:02:38,580 --> 01:02:41,938
<i>Mom, what did they do
to you and Dad when-</i>

739
01:02:41,971 --> 01:02:44,113
Shh. It's all in the past.

740
01:02:44,114 --> 01:02:47,085
There's nothing you can do.
It was meant to be.

741
01:02:47,086 --> 01:02:50,385
<i>I was so upset,
so angry at you for leaving me.</i>

742
01:02:50,386 --> 01:02:52,303
Plea- Please
don't abandon me again.

743
01:02:52,304 --> 01:02:54,894
Forgive me, little Sarah.

744
01:02:54,895 --> 01:02:57,452
I can't speak anymore.

745
01:02:57,453 --> 01:03:00,365
<i>I belong to another place now.
Use your gifts.</i>

746
01:03:00,401 --> 01:03:02,729
Use them. Use them.

747
01:03:02,730 --> 01:03:04,716
<i>Mommy.</i>

748
01:03:04,717 --> 01:03:06,636
[Gasping]

749
01:03:06,637 --> 01:03:10,313
<i>Okay, guys, listen up.
We're looking for a girl around 28.</i>

750
01:03:10,314 --> 01:03:14,567
Her name is Sarah Mandy.
If you see her, don't approach her.

751
01:03:18,729 --> 01:03:20,676
Michael?

752
01:03:20,677 --> 01:03:23,649
Michael. Mi-

753
01:03:24,136 --> 01:03:27,646
Michael! Michael!

754
01:03:29,925 --> 01:03:32,312
Michael, stop!

755
01:03:33,154 --> 01:03:35,262
Michael?

756
01:03:37,603 --> 01:03:39,874
- [Coughing, Wheezing]
- Michael.

757
01:03:39,875 --> 01:03:42,080
Are you okay?

758
01:03:42,081 --> 01:03:43,998
Michael, you're sick.

759
01:03:43,999 --> 01:03:46,593
Where's Paul?

760
01:03:46,594 --> 01:03:48,510
I thought-

761
01:03:48,511 --> 01:03:50,429
did you-

762
01:03:50,430 --> 01:03:52,510
I think-

763
01:03:52,511 --> 01:03:56,732
I think he's -
I think he's dead.

764
01:03:56,733 --> 01:03:59,326
- Oh, my God.
- They killed him.

765
01:03:59,327 --> 01:04:01,242
- Oh, my God.
- And I can't -

766
01:04:01,243 --> 01:04:04,757
I don't want to talk about that now.

767
01:04:05,753 --> 01:04:07,672
Let's go.

768
01:04:07,673 --> 01:04:09,594
My apartment is not safe.

769
01:04:09,595 --> 01:04:12,471
- Everywhere I go, they-
- We'll go to my place.

770
01:04:12,472 --> 01:04:14,711
They won't look for you there.

771
01:04:14,712 --> 01:04:17,196
[Coughing]

772
01:04:19,509 --> 01:04:21,494
No, no. No lights.

773
01:04:21,495 --> 01:04:23,412
Why?

774
01:04:23,413 --> 01:04:26,194
We don't want them to see us.

775
01:04:26,838 --> 01:04:28,755
[Coughing Continues]

776
01:04:28,756 --> 01:04:32,104
I'm so happy
we found each other.

777
01:04:33,395 --> 01:04:35,795
Are you okay?

778
01:04:35,796 --> 01:04:39,503
- Why don't you just rest, take off your coat-
- No, no, no.

779
01:04:40,112 --> 01:04:42,030
I'm freezing. Sorry.
I'm freezing.

780
01:04:42,031 --> 01:04:44,912
I just haven't spent a-
a single night inside.

781
01:04:44,913 --> 01:04:47,309
- I looked everywhere for him.
- Yeah, what happened?

782
01:04:47,310 --> 01:04:50,659
- Because I went to Monteleone to find you.
- I couldn't get there.

783
01:04:51,758 --> 01:04:54,284
They were following me.

784
01:04:54,285 --> 01:04:58,411
Everything you were trying to tell me
I understand now.

785
01:04:58,412 --> 01:05:00,555
I'm sorry I didn't believe you.

786
01:05:00,556 --> 01:05:02,411
I'm really sorry.

787
01:05:02,412 --> 01:05:04,797
Okay.

788
01:05:05,353 --> 01:05:07,914
Maybe you shouldn't smoke.

789
01:05:07,915 --> 01:05:09,991
- Why don't you-
- [Grunts]

790
01:05:09,992 --> 01:05:13,415
do you want me to fix something?
Tea, maybe?

791
01:05:13,416 --> 01:05:15,804
[Coughs]
No.

792
01:05:17,606 --> 01:05:20,006
No, I'm f- I'm fine.

793
01:05:20,007 --> 01:05:22,980
I'm just-

794
01:05:22,981 --> 01:05:26,210
I'm just pleased
I found you again.

795
01:05:26,211 --> 01:05:29,407
I'm fine.
don't worry. Fine.

796
01:05:30,019 --> 01:05:32,885
[Coughing Continues]

797
01:05:34,721 --> 01:05:37,621
<i>Michael, you're bleeding!</i>

798
01:05:40,032 --> 01:05:42,623
[Gasps]

799
01:05:42,624 --> 01:05:45,886
<i>- It's nothing.
- Michael, you're hurt!</i>

800
01:05:45,887 --> 01:05:47,934
No, it's - it's okay.

801
01:05:47,935 --> 01:05:50,012
It's nothing.

802
01:05:50,013 --> 01:05:52,412
What do you mean, it's nothing?
You're hurt!

803
01:05:52,413 --> 01:05:54,811
I told you it's nothing!
Get off me!

804
01:05:54,812 --> 01:05:58,170
<i>- [Gasping]
- I told you to get the fuck off me!</i>

805
01:05:58,171 --> 01:06:00,537
<i>- [Gagging]
- [Screams]</i>

806
01:06:03,481 --> 01:06:06,326
[Groans]

807
01:06:07,513 --> 01:06:12,693
<i>Do you think they would
spare me and my child?</i>

808
01:06:12,694 --> 01:06:15,831
You're so naive.

809
01:06:15,832 --> 01:06:17,747
You can't escape her.

810
01:06:17,748 --> 01:06:19,475
But they killed your son!

811
01:06:19,476 --> 01:06:23,986
Your mother can't
help you anymore.

812
01:06:23,987 --> 01:06:27,170
We all have one mother now.

813
01:06:27,205 --> 01:06:30,353
<i>The Mother of Tears.</i>

814
01:06:30,387 --> 01:06:32,242
<i>[Screaming]</i>

815
01:06:32,243 --> 01:06:35,753
You bitch!
Oh, you crazy-

816
01:06:35,949 --> 01:06:38,800
<i>you crazy bitch!</i>

817
01:06:40,240 --> 01:06:43,565
<i>[Screaming Continues]</i>

818
01:07:05,736 --> 01:07:09,284
Guglielmo.
The name Marta gave you.

819
01:07:09,285 --> 01:07:11,674
Find him.

820
01:07:12,263 --> 01:07:15,555
[Gasps]

821
01:07:19,909 --> 01:07:22,241
[Groaning]

822
01:07:22,242 --> 01:07:25,091
Mommy!

823
01:07:25,092 --> 01:07:27,392
Sarah!

824
01:07:29,089 --> 01:07:31,957
[Whimpers]

825
01:07:34,847 --> 01:07:37,882
[Sobbing]

826
01:08:04,991 --> 01:08:07,882
<i>[TV: Anchorman]
Welcome back to the morning news.</i>

827
01:08:07,883 --> 01:08:09,808
<i>And now for today's top story.</i>

828
01:08:09,809 --> 01:08:12,826
<i>They're calling it
the second fall of Rome.</i>

829
01:08:12,827 --> 01:08:15,826
Over the past few days the city
has witnessed hundreds of acts of violence.

830
01:08:15,827 --> 01:08:19,293
Detective Marchi,
you say that they are all connected?

831
01:08:19,294 --> 01:08:20,537
Uh, yes...

832
01:08:20,538 --> 01:08:23,930
everything started with events
at the Art Museum of Rome.

833
01:08:24,331 --> 01:08:28,156
The brutal murder of the assistant curator,
Giselle Mares.

834
01:08:28,157 --> 01:08:30,446
<i>But how does that all tie together?</i>

835
01:08:30,447 --> 01:08:32,722
It was the trigger for everything
that's happening now.

836
01:08:32,723 --> 01:08:36,722
We ask everybody to be on the lookout
for this girl, Sarah Mandy...

837
01:08:36,723 --> 01:08:40,036
<i>the only witness
to events at the museum.</i>

838
01:08:40,037 --> 01:08:42,374
- If you see her-
- Is she a suspect?

839
01:08:42,375 --> 01:08:44,623
If you see her,
do not approach her.

840
01:08:44,624 --> 01:08:47,835
<i>Call the police
and ask to speak to Homicide.</i>

841
01:08:47,836 --> 01:08:49,245
Shit!

842
01:08:49,246 --> 01:08:52,797
[Horns Honking]

843
01:08:52,798 --> 01:08:55,679
<i>- [Man ¶1] Fuck you!
- [Man ¶2] Oh, no, fuck you!</i>

844
01:08:55,680 --> 01:08:59,658
<i>- [Man ¶3] Give me my money!
- What are you talking about?</i>

845
01:09:00,870 --> 01:09:03,941
- Give me your car. Give me your car!
- [Woman Screams]

846
01:09:03,942 --> 01:09:06,568
[All Shouting, Screaming]

847
01:09:06,569 --> 01:09:09,260
Sunglasses!

848
01:09:10,412 --> 01:09:13,814
[Screaming]
No! No! No!

849
01:09:23,028 --> 01:09:24,750
Hello?

850
01:09:24,751 --> 01:09:27,925
Yes, can I please have the address
for Mr. Guglielmo De-Witt?

851
01:09:27,926 --> 01:09:31,003
D, e, w, i, double t.

852
01:09:31,104 --> 01:09:35,652
<i>[Dogs Barking]</i>

853
01:09:39,871 --> 01:09:42,891
<i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>

854
01:09:49,481 --> 01:09:52,367
- Yes?
- I need to see Guglielmo De-Witt.

855
01:09:52,368 --> 01:09:55,658
[Scoffs]
And you are?

856
01:09:55,659 --> 01:09:59,124
My name won't mean
anything to him.

857
01:10:00,497 --> 01:10:03,763
All right. Come in.

858
01:10:31,043 --> 01:10:34,118
So, you wanted to see me?

859
01:10:34,119 --> 01:10:36,808
Please sit down.

860
01:10:38,410 --> 01:10:42,250
As you can see, I-
I'm not very mobile.

861
01:10:42,251 --> 01:10:45,679
I'm here because I-
I have to ask you about-

862
01:10:45,680 --> 01:10:49,688
[Groaning]

863
01:10:53,941 --> 01:10:58,777
<i>We alchemists may practice
an ancient art...</i>

864
01:10:58,778 --> 01:11:01,530
but we do watch the news.

865
01:11:01,531 --> 01:11:05,275
do you think I wouldn't know
who you are, Sarah Mandy?

866
01:11:05,276 --> 01:11:09,599
And that the police is looking for you
because you're wanted for murder?

867
01:11:09,600 --> 01:11:11,517
[Whimpering]

868
01:11:11,518 --> 01:11:13,763
<i>Another thing
about us alchemists-</i>

869
01:11:13,764 --> 01:11:16,517
<i>we're not all one
thing or another.</i>

870
01:11:16,518 --> 01:11:21,477
After all, good magic is good,
and black magic is-

871
01:11:21,478 --> 01:11:24,555
<i>[Chuckles]</i>

872
01:11:24,556 --> 01:11:26,892
Well, it's good too.

873
01:11:26,893 --> 01:11:28,908
<i>Some of what we do
is magic, science...</i>

874
01:11:28,909 --> 01:11:32,528
esoterism, theosophy, natural law.

875
01:11:32,529 --> 01:11:37,240
<i>A little of this and a little of that.</i>

876
01:11:50,398 --> 01:11:55,424
<i>This will let me know
who you really are...</i>

877
01:11:55,425 --> 01:11:57,376
and what you've really seen.

878
01:11:57,377 --> 01:11:59,299
[Grunting]

879
01:11:59,300 --> 01:12:01,157
<i>Hmm. Interesting.</i>

880
01:12:01,158 --> 01:12:03,012
<i>I see you have latent powers.</i>

881
01:12:03,013 --> 01:12:06,894
Instinct more than anything else.

882
01:12:07,081 --> 01:12:09,320
<i>Marta Colussi sent you, I see.</i>

883
01:12:09,321 --> 01:12:12,525
<i>So did your mother,
Elisa Mandy.</i>

884
01:12:12,526 --> 01:12:15,377
[Chuckles]

885
01:12:18,130 --> 01:12:21,778
- [Blows]
- [Gasps]

886
01:12:23,283 --> 01:12:25,621
What did you do to me? Huh?

887
01:12:25,622 --> 01:12:31,224
did you expect me to just let you waltz
in here without making sure who you are?

888
01:12:31,225 --> 01:12:33,627
[Chuckles]

889
01:12:33,628 --> 01:12:37,986
<i>Now, why exactly
did you come here?</i>

890
01:12:38,590 --> 01:12:40,898
I need to find
the Mother of Tears.

891
01:12:40,899 --> 01:12:43,263
<i>- Why?
- Look what's happening to the city.</i>

892
01:12:43,264 --> 01:12:46,310
Rome is falling apart.
She has to be stopped.

893
01:12:46,311 --> 01:12:52,078
Mmm. What do you think
you can do? Kill her?

894
01:12:53,832 --> 01:12:57,740
Well, my mother was very powerful...

895
01:12:57,741 --> 01:13:00,621
and I think I might
have the same gifts.

896
01:13:00,622 --> 01:13:03,926
Which you found out about
when? Yesterday?

897
01:13:04,658 --> 01:13:06,769
I don't know.

898
01:13:06,770 --> 01:13:11,808
There's got to be some people that can help,
people like my mother.

899
01:13:12,598 --> 01:13:15,447
Father Johannes said that-

900
01:13:15,448 --> 01:13:19,035
that Mater Lacrimarum is bringing
on the Second Age of Witches.

901
01:13:19,036 --> 01:13:22,172
Mmm.
Father Johannes was right.

902
01:13:22,173 --> 01:13:26,400
Somewhere in the city the celebration
has already begun.

903
01:13:26,401 --> 01:13:28,898
But I'm afraid there is no
army of good witches

904
01:13:28,899 --> 01:13:30,691
out there to come to the rescue.

905
01:13:30,692 --> 01:13:34,211
If you want to stop her,
you have to do it yourself.

906
01:13:34,212 --> 01:13:36,454
So I'm on my own now?

907
01:13:36,455 --> 01:13:38,377
I didn't say I wouldn't help.

908
01:13:38,378 --> 01:13:42,060
I can't give you answers,
but I can share information.

909
01:13:42,061 --> 01:13:44,461
Follow me.

910
01:13:44,462 --> 01:13:49,487
Centuries ago, a great Roman alchemist
named Varelli...

911
01:13:49,488 --> 01:13:52,498
lived for a time in this villa.

912
01:13:52,499 --> 01:13:55,477
He was also a gifted architect.

913
01:13:55,478 --> 01:14:01,476
And near the end of his life, he built
the residences for the Three Mothers.

914
01:14:12,780 --> 01:14:16,161
This may tell you
something you need to know.

915
01:14:35,090 --> 01:14:38,219
<i>[Man Reading]
The Three Mothers.</i>

916
01:14:39,668 --> 01:14:42,609
<i>I don't know
how much it will cost me...</i>

917
01:14:42,643 --> 01:14:47,566
<i>to break what we alchemists
have always called SILENTIUM.</i>

918
01:14:51,672 --> 01:14:53,589
<i>[Man Continues]
I met the three Mothers...</i>

919
01:14:53,590 --> 01:14:55,639
<i>and built three houses
for them:</i>

920
01:14:55,640 --> 01:14:58,680
<i>one in Freiburg,
one in New York...</i>

921
01:14:58,681 --> 01:15:01,304
<i>and one in Rome.</i>

922
01:15:01,305 --> 01:15:06,202
<i>I discovered too late that these houses
hide obscene secrets.</i>

923
01:15:06,203 --> 01:15:09,723
<i>It is from here
that the sisters spread pain...</i>

924
01:15:09,724 --> 01:15:13,302
<i>tears and darkness
throughout the world.</i>

925
01:15:20,031 --> 01:15:24,221
<i>This building should be
the one Varelli built in Rome.</i>

926
01:15:25,345 --> 01:15:27,857
<i>[Sarah]
"What you see...</i>

927
01:15:27,892 --> 01:15:30,369
<i>"does not exist...</i>

928
01:15:30,370 --> 01:15:34,401
<i>and what you cannot
see is truth. "</i>

929
01:15:34,402 --> 01:15:36,932
It's a riddle.

930
01:15:36,933 --> 01:15:39,683
Find where Mater Lacrimarum resides...

931
01:15:39,684 --> 01:15:41,764
<i>and you'll find the answer.</i>

932
01:15:41,765 --> 01:15:44,734
<i>Are you sure
you want to do this?</i>

933
01:15:45,637 --> 01:15:48,231
- do I have a choice?
- [Chuckles]

934
01:15:48,232 --> 01:15:52,639
<i>- [Horns Honking]
- [People Screaming, Grunting]</i>

935
01:16:44,760 --> 01:16:48,664
<i>[Man, Echoing]
Mater.</i>

936
01:16:48,665 --> 01:16:50,584
<i>Mater.</i>

937
01:16:50,585 --> 01:16:52,891
<i>Mater.</i>

938
01:16:52,892 --> 01:16:55,227
<i>Mater.</i>

939
01:16:55,228 --> 01:16:58,197
[Chattering, Laughing]

940
01:16:59,581 --> 01:17:01,756
Stop. Stop right here!

941
01:17:01,757 --> 01:17:05,586
[Chattering,
Laughing Continue]

942
01:18:28,983 --> 01:18:31,700
- [Gasping]
- [Wings Fluttering]

943
01:18:32,952 --> 01:18:35,823
<i>- [Gasping]
- [Wings Fluttering]</i>

944
01:20:53,220 --> 01:20:55,873
- Hey! Who are you?
- [Gasps]

945
01:20:55,874 --> 01:20:58,821
I, uh- I just saw
some women come in.

946
01:20:58,822 --> 01:21:00,741
- did you see them?
- No.

947
01:21:00,742 --> 01:21:04,004
- You here to interview me?
- Yeah.

948
01:21:04,615 --> 01:21:06,533
Here.

949
01:21:06,534 --> 01:21:08,453
How long you've been living here?

950
01:21:08,454 --> 01:21:10,761
Shh-A long time.

951
01:21:10,762 --> 01:21:13,447
Thirty, forty years.

952
01:21:13,448 --> 01:21:18,793
Since the Nazis escaped
at the end of the war.

953
01:21:18,794 --> 01:21:21,995
And who used to live here
before you?

954
01:21:21,996 --> 01:21:25,643
<i>Oh, I don't know.
A kind of association.</i>

955
01:21:25,644 --> 01:21:29,293
<i>Philosophers. Artists maybe.
I don't remember.</i>

956
01:21:29,294 --> 01:21:31,276
Why did they leave?

957
01:21:31,277 --> 01:21:34,447
Maybe because when the Nazis
occupied the villa...

958
01:21:34,448 --> 01:21:38,127
<i>they tortured and killed
a lot of people down here.</i>

959
01:21:38,128 --> 01:21:42,186
<i>Hey! You won't
report me, will ya?</i>

960
01:21:58,168 --> 01:22:00,173
Shh, shh.

961
01:22:01,143 --> 01:22:03,063
[Whispers]
Easy.

962
01:22:03,064 --> 01:22:06,167
<i>[Door Sliding Closed]</i>

963
01:22:06,168 --> 01:22:09,747
<i>[Footsteps]</i>

964
01:22:13,595 --> 01:22:17,172
- Where did she go?
- I think she's gone.

965
01:22:19,068 --> 01:22:20,990
[Knife Blade Rings]

966
01:22:20,991 --> 01:22:22,939
I'll check upstairs.

967
01:22:22,940 --> 01:22:25,625
- Stay here.
- Yeah.

968
01:22:36,676 --> 01:22:40,192
- She's not there!
- Then she's gone. Everything's okay.

969
01:22:40,193 --> 01:22:43,396
You forgot what we were supposed to do,
didn't you?

970
01:22:43,397 --> 01:22:45,316
- No.
- No?

971
01:22:45,317 --> 01:22:50,980
Inform them every time somebody
comes to look around!

972
01:22:50,981 --> 01:22:53,832
- Understand?
- Yes!

973
01:22:53,833 --> 01:22:56,219
- Yes.
- Move!

974
01:22:56,871 --> 01:22:59,107
<i>[Footsteps Receding]</i>

975
01:23:08,778 --> 01:23:11,650
- Where did they go? They just-
